Install EPEL Repository;
$ dnf install https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-release-latest-8.noarch.rpm Install Ansible;
$ yum install ansible Download Ansible Tower;
$ mkdir /tmp/ansible-tower-setup $ cd /tmp/ansible-tower-setup $ curl -k -O https://releases.ansible.com/ansible-tower/setup/ansible-tower-setup-latest. tar.gz $ tar xvf ansible-tower-setup-latest.tar.gz $ cd /ansible-tower-setup-x.x.x-x Modify inventory file and add the following;
$ vi inventory [tower] server1.example.com server2.example.com [all:vars] admin_password=&#39;&#39; [database] pg_database=&#39;awx&#39; pg_username=&#39;awx&#39; pg_password=&#39;&#39; Install Ansible Tower (this will run install.yml playbook)
$ ./setup.sh Copy your certificate/key to the following location;

Install using USB media Link to heading A. Create a bootable USB drive using your computer
Download the image from https://downloads.f5.com/ into you computer
Mount the image;
# mkdir /mnt/cd # mount -o loop /shared/images/BIGIP-13.1.1.5-0.0.4.iso /mnt/cd mount: /shared/images/BIGIP-13.1.1.5-0.0.4.iso is write-protected, mounting read-only Insert a USB disk and run mkdisk script;
# cd /mnt/cd # ./mkdisk In the next step, F5 will ask you the following questions. Answer as appropriate to your environment;

Symmetric key encryption Link to heading Create a sample text file which will be encrypted;
# echo Plain Text &gt; input.txt # cat input.txt Plain Text Encrypt input.txt file;
# gpg -c input.txt gpg: directory `/home/user1/.gnupg' created gpg: new configuration file `/home/user1/.gnupg/gpg.conf' created gpg: WARNING: options in `/home/user1/.gnupg/gpg.conf' are not yet active during this run If you are using GPG for the first time on this server, it will ask to set a passphrase.

Download SharePoint 2016 update releases from Microsoft website;
https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/mt715807(v=office.16).aspx.
Check Todd Klindt’s website to find what type of updates each version has including the build number;
http://www.toddklindt.com/blog/Builds/SharePoint-2016-Builds.aspx
Open SharePoint 2016 Management Shell and run the following command to take a full backup of the current farm;
PS &gt; Backup-SPFarm -Directory &lt;BackupFolder&gt; -BackupMethod Full -Verbose Stop Search Service Application on the Search servers since we do not want Search to crawl while patching.
